&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3967&quot; title=&quot;IllegalArgumentException: Illegal Capacity: -1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-3967&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-3967&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: skip compressed streams if required values aren&apos;t present&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16207912" author="lehmi" created="Tue, 17 Oct 2017 16:58:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; for the analysis. IMHO the best idea is to skip such streams as this is already a part of the brute force search and we won&apos;t give up to early.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Set to resolved&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
